[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":175},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F18\u002Fscss-handbook-3-operators\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F18\u002Fscss-handbook-3-operators\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F18\u002Fscss-handbook-3-operators\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F18\u002Fscss-handbook-3-operators\u002F":151,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F18\u002Fscss-handbook-3-operators\u002F":160},"\u002FSCSS\u002F20190418\u002F2434021097\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":8,"body":9,"category":134,"date":135,"description":136,"extension":137,"lang":138,"meta":139,"navigation":140,"path":141,"readingMinutes":142,"seo":143,"standalone":144,"stem":145,"tags":146,"tldr":148,"updated":148,"url":149,"__hash__":150},"content\u002Fen\u002FSCSS\u002Fscss-handbook-3-operators.md","SCSS Handbook (3) — Operators","4340210972","\u002Fscss\u002F20190418\u002F2434021097\u002F",{"type":10,"value":11,"toc":128},"minimark",[12,17,21,25,28,36,43,50,55,58,67,70,73,80,85,91,102,107,114,119,122],[13,14,16],"h2",{"id":15},"intro","Intro",[18,19,20],"p",{},"Operators? Like add, subtract, multiply, divide?\nSCSS supports operators: add (+), subtract (-), multiply (*), divide (\u002F).",[13,22,24],{"id":23},"operators","Operators",[18,26,27],{},"If you can use operators well in SCSS, not only can you ditch the calculator (lol), you can also offload some mental math and speed up development.",[18,29,30,31,35],{},"Say today's layout width is 1180. We can use operators to auto-calculate the ",[32,33,34],"code",{},"px"," value for each column:",[18,37,38],{},[39,40],"img",{"alt":41,"src":42},"image","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F7YWRXiL.png",[18,44,45,46,49],{},"Normally ",[32,47,48],{},"1180 \u002F 3"," isn't a clean integer, but SCSS gets as close as it can. So in the browser's CSS panel, you'll see a really long number:",[18,51,52],{},[39,53],{"alt":41,"src":54},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FnOMHBXP.png",[18,56,57],{},"Using operators properly helps you ditch the calculator and get pixel-perfect values. Later we'll combine operators with variables — building up SCSS familiarity post by post.",[18,59,60],{},[61,62,66],"a",{"href":63,"rel":64},"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FxMMXLq",[65],"nofollow","CodePen",[18,68,69],{},"A quick extra exercise:",[18,71,72],{},"Default web font size is usually around 14-16px. If certain sections need different font sizes, you wouldn't define a variable for each size — that's inefficient. Usually you set one main font size and use operators to adjust.",[18,74,75,76,79],{},"Here's the baseline — a main ",[32,77,78],{},"font-size: 16px"," and three classes:",[18,81,82],{},[39,83],{"alt":41,"src":84},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FoSulZwE.png",[18,86,87,88,90],{},"The result is unsurprising — all ",[32,89,78],{},".",[18,92,93,94,97,98,101],{},"Now if ",[32,95,96],{},"font-size2"," should be 40px and ",[32,99,100],{},"font-size3"," should be 10px, we'd write:",[18,103,104],{},[39,105],{"alt":41,"src":106},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FclInE14.png",[18,108,109,110,113],{},"One thing to watch out for with operators — the minus sign (",[32,111,112],{},"-",") can cause issues, because SCSS can't always tell whether it's a variable or a subtraction expression. So I'd recommend always putting spaces around operators to avoid errors:",[18,115,116],{},[39,117],{"alt":41,"src":118},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FbVjaiX9.png",[18,120,121],{},"Correct usage:",[18,123,124],{},[61,125,66],{"href":126,"rel":127},"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FommGGo",[65],{"title":129,"searchDepth":130,"depth":130,"links":131},"",2,[132,133],{"id":15,"depth":130,"text":16},{"id":23,"depth":130,"text":24},"SCSS","2019-04-18 17:24:30","Operators? Like add, subtract, multiply, divide? Yep — SCSS supports operators: add (+), subtract (-), multiply (*), and divide (\u002F).","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002Fscss-handbook-3-operators","1",{"title":6,"description":136},false,"en\u002FSCSS\u002Fscss-handbook-3-operators",[134,147],"SCSS Handbook",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F18\u002Fscss-handbook-3-operators\u002F","R2h0uMfKKwaEvlcFicKbWPTHCYFcaqsJIiOJxadvdLs",{"newer":152,"older":156},{"url":153,"title":154,"date":155},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F18\u002Fjavascript-this-keyword-explained\u002F","this Is the Weirdest Thing in JavaScript — Here's How I Finally Got It","2019-04-18 19:46:16",{"url":157,"title":158,"date":159},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F18\u002Fjavascript-merge-array-object-properties\u002F","How I Merged Array Object Properties in JavaScript (and Burned 4 Hours Doing It)","2019-04-18 16:00:00",[161,166,171],{"url":162,"title":163,"date":164,"readingMinutes":165},"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2025\u002F11\u002F23\u002Fsass-deprecated-import-use-forward-migration\u002F","SCSS Is Deprecating @import?!","2025-11-23 15:32:01","4",{"url":167,"title":168,"date":169,"readingMinutes":170},"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F21\u002Fscss-handbook-5-mixin\u002F","SCSS Handbook (5) — mixin","2019-04-21 07:24:30","2",{"url":172,"title":173,"date":174,"readingMinutes":170},"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F19\u002Fscss-handbook-4-import\u002F","SCSS Handbook (4) — @import","2019-04-19 17:24:30",1784087342152]